[JE virus is endemic in northeastern India, where the JE virus transmission season is beginning. Fogging is not an effective long-term approach to JE prevention; vaccination is.

It is odd that Manipur has an active JE vaccination initiative yet the Odisha health authorities indicate incorrectly that there is no vaccine. Vaccination is the most effective preventive measure. Vector control may provide short-term mosquito population reduction but is not a long-term preventive measure. Extensive rice fields and other wetlands offer ample breeding sites. The Odisha report mentions acute encephalitis syndrome, some cases of which are due to JE virus infections, and several other etiologies have been proposed for other AES cases.

Maps of India can be accessed at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4368952,306. - Mod.TY

